==English==
====Etymology====
From Greek [[ἐπιφάνεια]], [[-εια]] feminine of [[ἐπιφαίνω]] "appear" ([[ἐπι-]] + [[φαίνω]] "shine, appear").

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-epiphany.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|epiphanies}}

# a [[manifestation]] or [[appearance]] of a [[divine]] or [[superhuman]] [[being]]
# an illuminating [[discovery]] often resulting in a personal feeling of elation
# season or time of the Christian church year from the Epiphany feast day to [[Mardi Gras]] ([[Shrove Tuesday]]), the day before [[Ash Wednesday]], the start of [[Lent]] (See [[Epiphany]])

